In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. declares that it is in the national interest of the United States to provide assistance for unexpected urgent refugee and migration needs in the Western Hemisphere. The President determines that an amount not exceeding $50.3 million will be allocated from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund. This assistance may include contributions to international organizations by the Department of State's Bureau of Population, Refugees, and Migration. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to submit this determination to Congress, along with the accompanying justification, and to publish it in the Federal Register.